# WFM-Synthetic-Data-Lab ⚡️

[![DATA: SYNTHETIC ONLY](https://img.shields.io/badge/DATA-SYNTHETIC%20ONLY-red)](#synthetic-safety) [![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10%2B-blue)](#quickstart) [![CLI](https://img.shields.io/badge/CLI-wfm--synth-black)](#cli) [![UKG Pro WFM](https://img.shields.io/badge/UKG-Pro%20WFM%20%2F%20DataHub-6f2dbd)](#why-this-exists)

> **This repo is the power plant.**\
> It generates *table-accurate*, *schema-driven*, *join-safe* synthetic UKG Pro WFM / DataHub-style datasets so every other repo in the portfolio can run **without** access to real enterprise data.

If you’re looking for the “how the hell did he do that?” moment: this is it.\
Every visitor gets a fresh dataset experience (random seed mode) unless you explicitly lock it to deterministic (fixed seed).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Why this exists {#why-this-exists}

UKG WFM analytics portfolios usually die in one of two places: 1) “I can’t share the data”\
2) “My fake data doesn’t join to anything”

This repo solves both by generating synthetic **people + org structure + time & labor facts** that: - look realistic (human names, email patterns, plausible hours) - follow the *same* schema as real DataHub tables (from the Omni dictionary) - preserve org-path patterns and keys (facility/unit/cost center) - can scale from “1 day / 10 employees” to “24 months / 310 employees / multi-unit facilities”

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## What you can generate (today)

Pack-run (multiple tables in one shot): - `vDimBusinessStructure` - `vTimecardTotal` - `vAccrualBalance`

The design supports expanding to 350+ tables via schema snapshots + generator registry.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Synthetic safety {#synthetic-safety}

-   ✅ No real employee data
-   ✅ No PHI/PII from any organization
-   ✅ Faker-generated names & emails (realistic, not cartoon characters)
-   ✅ Output changes on every run by default (**seed_mode: random**)

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Architecture (how the power gets made)

```mermaid
flowchart LR

  A[Omni Data Dictionary XLSX] --> B[Schema Snapshot JSON]
  B --> C[Profiles + Column Mapping]
  D[Scenario YAML] --> E[Generator Engine]

  C --> E
  E --> F[Output Pack: CSV + metadata]
  F --> G[Downstream Repos: BI / SQL / ML / Notebooks]
```
 
